The code looks like:

try {
	projectName= debugTarget.getLaunch().getLaunchConfiguration
().getAttribute(IJavaLaunchConfigurationConstants.ATTR_PROJECT_NAME, (String) 
null);
} catch (CoreException e) {
	throw new DebugException(e.getStatus());
}
IJavaProject project= JavaCore.create(root.getProject(projectName));


The problem is that a launch config does not have to be associated with a 
project (as RuntimeWorkbench configs, are not).

Options:
(1) Use project of associated type that was selected in the details preference.
(2) Use source lookup to find the type, and use the associated project.
